Section 16: Removing Spring Boot
    Lecture 83: Hibernate JPA Configuration


1. Add HibernateJPAAutoConfiguration property to change
 1.1 src/main/resources/application.properties file
    - add "spring.autoconfigure.exclude[3]=org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.orm.jpa.HibernateJpaAutoConfiguration"
           property in the application.properties file

2. Setup the New Hibernate JPA Config
 2.1 Create new HibernateJpaConfig.java
    - ej.springframework.config.HibernateJpaConfig.java
 3.2 Add spring context @Configuration annotation on the HibernateJpaConfig class
 3.3 Refer to Source code

4. Test
  3.1 Start Server
  3.2 Open localhost:8080
  3.3 Check Displayed data (i.e, Product list and Product items ...)
  3.4 Open H2-console browser
  3.5 login and check weather still working application and the h2 testdb database (i.e, PRODUCT Table)